  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001794.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Amar-Suena , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil in Nibru , the steadfast supporter of Enlil's temple , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters , erected the statue ( with the name ) \" It is him whose name was proclaimed by Suen who is the beloved of Urim \"."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001794.14",
      "line_range": "14",
      "translation": "(14) Whoever may transfer the statue ( erected ) for Ningal , the lady of Urim , this gold statue of mine ( from the temple ) to a storehouse , may Nanna , king of Urim , ( and ) Ningal , the mother of Urim , curse him ! May they cut short his lineage !"
    }
  ],
